You can use SDDS typography tokens in your Javascript application by importing the SASS file or use the ready-made CSS custom properties and classes.

In order to get the correct font file, make sure to install scania-theme.

```
> npm i @scania-sdds/theme-light

// And add c-theme component in your HTML
<c-theme name='scania' global='true'></c-theme>
```


**SASS**

We have a ready-to-use function to help you get the typography from SDDS colour library. Remember, you need to install `node-sass` in your application.

```
// First, import mixin and tokens file in your SASS environment
@import '~node_modules/@scania-sdds/typography/dist/scss/mixins';
@import '~node_modules/@scania-sdds/typography/dist/scss/tokens';

// use a mixin called type-style(token-name) to get typography properties from SDDS
.my-headline {
    @include type-style('headline-01');
}

// The code will be rendered as below
.my-headline {
  font-family: "Scania Sans Headline", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 10rem;
  line-height: 10rem;
  letter-spacing: 0em;
}
```

**CSS classes**

The format of CSS class is `sdds-{token-name}`.

In HTML file:

```
<p class="sdds-headline-01">
  This is a headline
</p>

```

You can use SDDS colour scale in your Javascript application by importing the SASS file or use the ready-made CSS custom properties and classes.


**SASS**

We have a ready-to-use function to help you get the colour from SDDS colour library. Remember, you need to install `node-sass` in your application.

```
// First, import the main file in your sass file
@import '~node_modules/@scania-sdds/colour/dist/scss/colour';

// use a function called get-colour(token-name) to get colour from SDDS colour scale
.my-div {
  color: get-colour(blue-900);
}

// The code will be rendered as below
.my-div {
  color: #041E42;
}
```

**CSS classes and CSS Custom Properties**

All colours are available if you install scania-theme and enable global properties. 

```<c-theme name='scania' global='true'></c-theme>```

Or, if you do not use scania-theme, you can import the main css from @scania-sdds/colour into your main css file. 
Then, you are ready to use the available classes and CSS variables in your CSS or HTML. Available properties for CSS classes are background and text colour. The format of CSS variables and classes, are always started with prefix `sdds-`.

```
// On your CSS file
// You don't need to do this if you use scania-theme
@import '~node_modules/@scania-sdds/colour/dist/css/colour.css';

.my-text{
   color: var(--sdds-blue-900);
}
```

In HTML file:

```
// Use this to style your element
// .sdds-{property}-{token-name}

<p class="sdds-text-blue-900 sdds-background-grey-200">
  An example paragraph
</p>

```
